CLASSICAL SWINE FEVER - RUSSIA (STAVROPOL)
******************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Thu 6 Sep 2007
Source: RIA Nakanune.ru [trans. by Corr.ArS, edited]
<http://www.nakanune.ru/news/2007/09/06/292703>

Pigs culled due to classical swine fever in Stavropol area
--------------------------------------------------------------------
A total of 252 pigs with the signs of [classical] swine fever [CSF]
have been slaughtered on a farm at the settlement Shturm, Stavropol
krai [region]. According to the information from the press and
information department of the Southern regional center, Ministry of
civilian defense and emergency situations, as provided to
Nakanune.ru, all other contact animals have been vaccinated,
There are 479 registered cases only. All the diseased animals are
slaughtered, the carcasses burned, covered by lime and 1.5 meters
[4.9 feet] of soil.
The 227 contact animals have been vaccinated by a hundred-fold
fortified vaccine. The buildings and the animals have been
disinfected. [How can live animals be disinfected?! clarifications
will be welcomed. - Mod.AS]
The Federal Inter-Regional Veterinary Laboratory has confirmed the
diagnosis; no new cases have been reported since.
A reminder: on 28 Aug 2007, 3 pigs have been found dead because of
this disease and there were 168 diseased animals in the same settlement.
--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[CSF is being documented within Russia's territory every year.
However, the number of endemically infected territories has decreased
due to preventive efforts. The following territories in the South
Federal Okrug of Russia are known to be infected: Volgograd,
Astrakhan and Krasnodar. -Mod.NP].
[A map of the Stavropol region is available at
<http://www.supertravelnet.com/maps/?action=selmap&country=241_8056_6&language=1>,
and the location of Shturm is available at
<http://www.fallingrain.com/world/RS/70/Shturm.html>. - Mod.AS]
